# WhatsApp connection reliability

- Use a **connection-first** model for WhatsApp automation delivery.
- Keep a background watchdog that periodically reconnects eligible workspace instances.
- Before any trigger workflow runs, attempt to ensure a workspace WhatsApp socket is connected.
- During sends, prefer waiting briefly for reconnection (bounded timeout) over immediate failure.
- Preserve clear user-facing failures when QR re-auth is required; do not hide real logged-out states.
- Do not remove/skip existing safeguards for persisted auth (`WA_AUTH_ROOT`) and backup/restore flow.
